{"summary":"Both amendments identify real correctness defects in milestone completion handling: one breaks recoverability after partial persistence failure, and the other persists a snapshot state the model explicitly marks invalid.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-3-b8dbc656","decision":"accept","rationale":"`update_task_run` seals the lineage entry before writing the snapshot and journal, while `FsTaskRunLineageStore::update_task_run` rejects any later finalize once the entry is terminal. If either follow-up write fails, retrying the same completion cannot repair the missing snapshot/journal mutation because the first step is no longer retryable. I could not find any milestone-specific reconcile path that actually repairs from lineage, so this is a real durability/idempotence bug."},{"amendment_id":"fr-3-9fecdf73","decision":"accept","rationale":"`record_bead_start` promotes the snapshot to `MilestoneStatus::Active` in the normal ready/planning path, but completion clears `active_bead` without moving status away from `Active` or validating semantics. `MilestoneSnapshot::validate_semantics` explicitly rejects `Active` with no `active_bead`, so completion can persist a state the model itself defines as inconsistent."}]}